    <note>Jin(1) Xchen [15532] The youngest son of Jin B [15530], he decided that since his elder brothers both earned the jinshi and were embarked on careers of public service that one brother had to remain and care for their parents, so he did not seek public office. According to Wang(2) Anshi, all four of the elder sons earned the jinshi, but only Junqing [470] is listed in the Jiangxi TZ. His wife, surname Xu(3) was also a Fuliang resident and none of her patrilineal ancestors of the previous three generations held office. Wang Anshi, WJ, 100.1033 (wife, surname Xu(3), who died in 1066 at age 77); Zeng Gong, WJ, 44.7b-9a. CBD, 2, 1424.</note>
